    <description>Tutanota is the world's most secure email service, easy to use and private by design. Sign up for free encrypted email now.

With end-to-end encryption and 2FA, your emails have never been more secure. The built-in encryption guarantees that your mailbox belongs to you: Nobody can decrypt or read your data.

**Please Note**: This is an automatically updated package. If you find it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s) and let them know the package is no longer updating correctly.</description>
    <summary>Tutanota is an email client with a strong focus on security and privacy that lets you encrypt emails on all your devices.</summary>
    <releaseNotes># What's new
 - Calendar default view [#10895](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10895)
 - Calendar Settings [#10893](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10893)

# Bugfixes
 - Calendar event from invite does not update [#10963](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10963)
 - First 100 mails disappear from conversation list after list reload [#10959](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10959)
 - Improve support for same event in different calendars [#10883](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10883)
 - importing ics files with duplicate altered instances throws an error, and import fails [#10851](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10851)
 - Delete an event after importing it in different calendars deletes the wrong entity [#10711](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10711)
 - Cannot send event update without organizer [#3288](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/3288)

# Milestone
https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/milestone/438?closed=1


